article.headline: Mississippi State advances to NIT semifinals at MSG

images.name: Bulldogs' Weatherspoon doing it all against Cardinals
images.caption: Mississippi State's Quinndary Weatherspoon has shown all facets of his game as he has lead helped the Bulldogs separate from Louisville in the NIT quarterfinal.

article.linkText: Mississippi State advances to NIT semifinals at MSG
article.story: LOUISVILLE, Ky. -- Quinndary Weatherspoon scored 19 points and grabbed 14 rebounds and Mississippi State advanced to the NIT semifinals at Madison Square Garden in New York with a 79-56 victory over Louisville on Tuesday night. Mississippi State (25-11) will face Penn State (24-13) on March 27. Lamar Peters opened the second quarter with a 3-pointer and Mississippi State led by at least nine points the rest of the way. Weatherspoon scored eight points during a 12-3 run to start the third for a 51-31 advantage and MSU cruised. Aric Holman added 16 points and eight rebounds for Mississippi State, which has won its most games since the 2009-10 season. Xavian Stapleton and Nick Weatherspoon each chipped in with 12 points. Abdul Ado had three blocks to tie Jarvis Varnado for the most blocks by a MSU freshman with 67. Ray Spalding paced Louisville (22-14) with 13 points and 11 rebounds for his 11th double-double of the season. The Cardinals shot 35 percent from the floor and were outrebounded 42-32. ---- More AP college basketball: https://collegebasketball.ap.org; https://twitter.com/AP-Top25 and https://www.podcastone.com/ap-sports-special-events
